{%- comment -%}
  Component: mallem-swatches
  Purpose: Render variant option swatches (color circles or label pills) on product cards
  Used in: snippets/mallem-product-card.liquid (after title, before price)

  Features:
  - Auto-detects color vs label mode from option name (color/colour/لون/couleur/farbe)
  - Color resolution: metafield JSON (server-side, exact + lowercase key) → CSS named-color fallback
  - Overflow truncation: show_count visible, rest hidden via .mallem-swatch--hidden CSS class
  - All variant image URLs pre-computed in Liquid — JS needs zero extra fetches at runtime
  - Active swatch tracks selected variant; sold-out swatches remain focusable (aria-disabled)

  Parameters:
  - product            {Object}  Required — Shopify product object
  - option_name        {String}  Optional — Option name to render (default: product.options[0])
  - swatch_type        {String}  Optional — "color" | "label" | "auto" (default: "auto")
  - show_count         {Number}  Optional — Max visible swatches before overflow (default: 5)
  - enable_hover_image {Boolean} Optional — Pass-through flag for JS hover preview (default: true)

  Metafield for accurate color swatches (optional but recommended):
  - Namespace: mallem | Key: swatch_colors | Type: JSON
  - Format: {"Black": "#1a1a1a", "Red": "#c8102e", "Navy": "#001f5b"}

  RTL: flex-wrap with logical properties handles RTL direction automatically.
  Performance: Image URLs and srcsets pre-built in Liquid; no /products.json calls at runtime.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  comment
    WHY allow_false on boolean: Liquid's | default filter treats `false` as falsy and
    would replace it with the default value — allow_false: true prevents this bug.
  endcomment
  assign option_name        = option_name | default: product.options[0]
  assign swatch_type        = swatch_type | default: 'auto'
  assign show_count         = show_count  | default: 5
  assign enable_hover_image = enable_hover_image | default: true, allow_false: true

  comment
    Find the option object by name to get its .values array and position index.
    Falling back to first option is defensive — handles typos in option_name param.
  endcomment
  assign option_to_render = nil
  assign option_index     = 0
  for opt in product.options_with_values
    if opt.name == option_name
      assign option_to_render = opt
      assign option_index     = forloop.index0
      break
    endif
  endfor

  if option_to_render == nil
    assign option_to_render = product.options_with_values[0]
    assign option_index     = 0
  endif

  comment
    WHY auto-detect swatch type: Merchants should not need to pass swatch_type manually.
    We infer from option name. Covering Arabic (لون), French (couleur), German (farbe)
    and both EN spellings ensures MENA and international merchants work out of the box.
  endcomment
  if swatch_type == 'auto'
    assign _opt_lower = option_to_render.name | downcase
    if _opt_lower contains 'color' or _opt_lower contains 'colour' or _opt_lower contains 'لون' or _opt_lower contains 'couleur' or _opt_lower contains 'farbe'
      assign resolved_type = 'color'
    else
      assign resolved_type = 'label'
    endif
  else
    assign resolved_type = swatch_type
  endif

  comment
    WHY .value on JSON metafield: Shopify returns the raw JSON string unless you call .value,
    which gives the already-parsed object. Key lookup then works with bracket notation.
    Merchants configure this once; every product with the metafield gets correct color dots.
  endcomment
  assign swatch_colors = product.metafields.mallem.swatch_colors.value

  comment
    Pre-compute overflow count before the loop so the "+N more" indicator is accurate.
  endcomment
  assign total_values   = option_to_render.values.size
  assign overflow_count = 0
  if total_values > show_count
    assign overflow_count = total_values | minus: show_count
  endif
-%}

{%- if option_to_render != nil and total_values > 1 -%}
  <div
    class="mallem-swatches mallem-swatches--{{ resolved_type }}"
    data-mallem-swatches-wrapper
    data-mallem-product-id="{{ product.id }}"
    data-mallem-option-index="{{ option_index }}"
    data-mallem-swatch-type="{{ resolved_type }}"
    data-mallem-enable-hover="{{ enable_hover_image }}"
    aria-label="{{ 'mallem.swatches.select_option' | t: option: option_to_render.name | escape }}"
    role="group"
  >
    {%- for value in option_to_render.values -%}
      {%- liquid
        comment
          Find the FIRST variant whose option at option_index matches the current value.
          variant.options[] is zero-indexed and maps directly to option_index.
          WHY first-match break: One variant per swatch is enough for image + availability.
          Other variants sharing this option value don't affect the card display.
        endcomment
        assign matched_variant = nil
        for variant in product.variants
          if variant.options[option_index] == value
            assign matched_variant = variant
            break
          endif
        endfor

        comment
          WHY nil guard on availability: product data can be incomplete on proxy-loaded
          recommendations; nil-safe check prevents Liquid exceptions.
        endcomment
        assign is_available = false
        if matched_variant != nil and matched_variant.available
          assign is_available = true
        endif

        comment
          WHY prefer variant.featured_image over product.featured_media:
          variant.featured_image is the image specifically shot for this color/style —
          showing it on hover converts better than a generic product hero image.
          Fallback to product.featured_media ensures we always have a URL to pass to JS.
        endcomment
        assign _variant_img = nil
        if matched_variant != nil and matched_variant.featured_image != nil
          assign _variant_img = matched_variant.featured_image
        elsif product.featured_media != nil
          assign _variant_img = product.featured_media
        endif

        comment
          WHY render ALL swatches (including overflow) with a CSS hidden class:
          JS needs all variant data (image URL, variant ID, availability) in the DOM.
          Completely skipping overflow swatches would require an AJAX fetch to get
          that data later — harmful to performance and complexity.
          CSS display:none via .mallem-swatch--hidden keeps them invisible but accessible.
        endcomment
        assign is_hidden = false
        if overflow_count > 0 and forloop.index > show_count
          assign is_hidden = true
        endif
      -%}

      {%- comment -%} Build srcset once — reused in data-image-srcset attribute below. {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- if _variant_img -%}
        {%- capture _srcset -%}{{ _variant_img | image_url: width: 300 }} 300w, {{ _variant_img | image_url: width: 600 }} 600w, {{ _variant_img | image_url: width: 900 }} 900w{%- endcapture -%}
        {%- assign _img_url = _variant_img | image_url: width: 600 -%}
      {%- else -%}
        {%- assign _srcset  = '' -%}
        {%- assign _img_url = '' -%}
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- comment -%}
        Color resolution order (server-side, no JS needed):
        1. Exact metafield key — as merchant typed it (e.g., "Navy")
        2. Lowercase metafield key — forgiving capitalization (e.g., "navy")
        3. CSS named-color fallback — works for standard English names ("black", "red")

        WHY not CSS names alone: Arabic brand names ("كحلي"), color codes, or multi-word
        names ("Coral Sand") will not parse as valid CSS colors — only metafield data helps.
        WHY server-side resolution: Avoids client-side JSON parse cost on every page load.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- if resolved_type == 'color' -%}
        {%- assign _swatch_bg = '' -%}
        {%- if swatch_colors != blank -%}
          {%- assign _swatch_bg = swatch_colors[value] -%}
          {%- if _swatch_bg == blank -%}
            {%- assign _val_lower = value | downcase -%}
            {%- assign _swatch_bg = swatch_colors[_val_lower] -%}
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if _swatch_bg == blank -%}
          {%- assign _swatch_bg = value | downcase -%}
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- comment -%}
        ARIA label: "Select Black (sold out)" gives keyboard users complete information
        in a single focus action — no need to navigate to a separate sold-out indicator.
        WHY aria-disabled not disabled: Sold-out swatches must remain keyboard-focusable
        so users discover the option exists. Hiding it causes surprise when it restocks.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- capture _aria_label -%}{{ 'mallem.swatches.select_option' | t: option: value }}{%- unless is_available %} {{ 'mallem.swatches.sold_out_suffix' | t }}{%- endunless -%}{%- endcapture -%}

      <button
        type="button"
        class="mallem-swatch mallem-swatch--{{ resolved_type }}{% if forloop.first %} mallem-swatch--active{% endif %}{% unless is_available %} mallem-swatch--sold-out{% endunless %}{% if is_hidden %} mallem-swatch--hidden{% endif %}"
        data-mallem-swatch
        data-variant-id="{{ matched_variant.id }}"
        data-value="{{ value | escape }}"
        data-available="{{ is_available }}"
        {% if _img_url != '' %}data-image-url="{{ _img_url }}"{% endif %}
        {% if _srcset != '' %}data-image-srcset="{{ _srcset | escape }}"{% endif %}
        {% if resolved_type == 'color' %}style="--swatch-color: {{ _swatch_bg | escape }}"{% endif %}
        aria-pressed="{% if forloop.first %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}"
        aria-label="{{ _aria_label | strip | escape }}"
        {% unless is_available %}aria-disabled="true"{% endunless %}
      >
        {%- comment -%}
          Label swatches render their text content; color swatches are purely visual
          (rendered as a circle via CSS ::before on the button).
          WHY no text in color swatch: The accessible name comes from aria-label,
          so an empty button is intentional and correct for screen readers.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- if resolved_type == 'label' -%}
          <span class="mallem-swatch__label">{{- value -}}</span>
        {%- endif -%}
      </button>
    {%- endfor -%}

    {%- if overflow_count > 0 -%}
      {%- comment -%}
        WHY aria-hidden: "+3 more" is decorative for sighted users only.
        Screen readers can discover all swatch buttons by navigating through them.
        This indicator only signals to sighted users that more options exist.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <span class="mallem-swatches__more" aria-hidden="true">
        + {{ 'mallem.swatches.more' | t: count: overflow_count }}
      </span>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>
{%- endif -%}
